article.headline: S. Dakota 84, Waldorf 59
article.story: VERMILLION, S.D. -- Karim Rowson scored 15 points to lead five South Dakota players in double figures in an 84-59 victory against Waldorf College on Saturday night. Tyler Flack added 14 points, Brandon Bos and Juevol Myles 12 each and Jordan Boots 11 for the Coyotes (3-3). Flack had seven rebounds and eight blocked shots. Robert Burns had 12 points and Jordan Nelson 11 for Waldorf, an NAIA school in Forest City, Iowa, that classified the game as an exhibition. The Warriors' record remained 1-5.
